<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf009983d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7425"><num value="7425">§ 7425.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf009983e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7425/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary to carry out this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf009983f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7425/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Limitation on expenditures for administrative expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Funds appropriated to carry out this subchapter may not be expended for the payment of expenses incurred by a board to administer an order.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf0099840-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/127/tV/s526">Pub. L. 104–127, title V, § 526</ref>, <date date="1996-04-04">Apr. 4, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/1048">110 Stat. 1048</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
